         <abstract>
            <p>This paper analyzes the financial performance of a unique sample (assembled from the files of three venture capitalists) of new or very young companies funded between 1960 and 1975. The study focuses on rates of return, failure rates, and diversification implications of portfolios characterized by the high degree of variability inherent in such investments.</p>
         </abstract>
